  <h1>Project Planner</h1>

  <p>Sassafras Tech Collective is looking for an energetic and focused project planner to join our diverse and growing team. We specifically need someone who can shepherd a software project from the early requirements gathering and design stages and into a clear set of user stories ready for development, and then continue to work with developers as the product is built, monitoring quality with each release. The job blends user experience, project/product management, and quality assurance skills. Specifically, it would include:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Extensive communication with clients to gather requirements</li>
    <li>Persona development</li>
    <li>User story authoring</li>
    <li>Wireframing</li>
    <li>Working with developers to ascertain technical feasibility and estimates</li>
    <li>Maintaining a high-level feature roadmap</li>
    <li>Maintaining the project backlog (task list)</li>
    <li>Triaging bug reports</li>
    <li>Managing developers and coordinating their work</li>
    <li>Translating new functionality requests into new features or changes to existing features</li>
    <li>Planning releases, managing scope, and setting order of task completion</li>
    <li>Testing new releases before delivery to client</li>
    <li>Writing documentation</li>
    <li>Managing the project budget</li>
  </ul>

  <p>As this broad list of competencies demonstrates, the applicant should be well-rounded and interested in participating in many aspects of a small tech consulting firm. Applicants should have a deep knowledge of what excellent software looks like and how it is made.</p>

  <p>The following skills would be an asset but are not required:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Graphic design skills</li>
    <li>Programming (Ruby on Rails, JavaScript)</li>
    <li>Server administration</li>
  </ul>

  <p>This position should be considered temporary for a period of 6 months, with a good likelihood of being made permanent and becoming a member-track position.</p>

