  <h2>About Sassafras</h2>
  <p>Sassafras Tech Collective is a tech consulting worker co-op based in Ann Arbor, MI. The worker co-op model is a different way of doing business that brings democracy into the workplace.</p>

  <p>We research, design, and develop technology projects that focus on social change and social justice. Some of our projects include work that focuses on:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Election observation systems in the Global South</li>
    <li>Local and democratic currencies</li>
    <li>Worker co-op micro loans in disadvantaged communities</li>
    <li>Ending gender/LGBTQ-based violence</li>
    <li>Health and disadvantaged communities</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Employees of Sassafras are initially considered "provisional members." They are expected to transition to full worker-ownership after an initial candidacy period of 6-12 months. All worker-owners have equal ownership of the co-op.</p>

  <p>Benefits include generous paid time off, health insurance, equipment allowances, flexible hours, and rad projects.</p>

  <p>We care deeply about social justice and the safety and conviviality of our office environment. See our <%= link_to 'Bylaws', bylaws_path %> and <%= link_to 'Code of Conduct', code_of_conduct_path %> for more information. We host a monthly social justice reading group and twice monthly social events. We also periodically go on group outings to social justice related events in Southeast Michigan.</p>

  <p>We have a preference for folks who are local to Ann Arbor, Michigan, but we are open to talking to remote folks as well. People traditionally underrepresented in the tech industry, especially women, LGBTQ folks, and men of color are strongly encouraged to apply.</p>

  <p>If you are interested, please send a resume to info@sassafras.coop. We look forward to hearing from you!</p>
